net.hudup.core.data

Class Unit

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.data.Unit

  • public class Unit
extends java.lang.Object
    Objects in framework such as profile, item profile, user profile, rating matrix, interchanged attribute map are stored in archives (files) of entire framework. Each archive (file) is called unit representing a CSV file, database table, Excel sheet, etc. This class just represents the name of unit but there are special classes processing on unit and so this class is identical to unit.
    Unit class has variable name representing its name and variable extra indicating whether or not this unit is essential one. If extra=true, this unit is extra (auxiliary) unit and so it is not essential unit. If extra=false, this unit is essential (important, main) unit such as rating matrix. The default value of this variable is extra=false, which means that a new unit is important one by default. When showing, the name of essential unit (extra=false) is shown within signs "<" and ">", for example, the name of rating unit is shown "<rating>".
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen
